featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Jalal Bukhari Dargah:-Jalal Bukhari Dargah, which is considered very sacred by the Muslim brothers, is located in the old town of Bodhan.

During the Islamic month of Safar, the Ursu festival is held for three days at this dargah. During these three days, many devotees from far and wide come here to pay their prayers (Niyaz). Also, Hindu devotees also come here and offer prayers.

About a thousand years ago "Hazrat Syed Shah Jalal Bukhari" from Buchira near Tashkent region came here to propagate Islam. Along with religious propaganda, he impressed the people here with his good behavior and earned a good reputation and was hailed as a great man.

Jalal Bukhari's tomb was built here after his death. It is called "Jalal Bukhari Dargah". It is known that during the rest of his life, a woman named Hirabai served him wholeheartedly, so after her death, her tomb was also built opposite Bukhari's tomb. Besides, there is a street named after her in the town. Today it is called Hiragalli.
